  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1SA 3:11" />¶ And the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> to <char style="w" strong="H8050">Samuel</char>, Behold, I will <char style="w" strong="H6213">do</char> a <char style="w" strong="H1697">thing</char> in <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, at which <char style="w" strong="H8147">both</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0241">ears</char> of every one that <char style="w" strong="H8085">heareth</char> it shall <char style="w" strong="H6750">tingle</char>. <verse eid="1SA 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1SA 3:12" />In that <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> I will <char style="w" strong="H6965">perform</char> against <char style="w" strong="H5941">Eli</char> all <char style="add">things</char> which I have <char style="w" strong="H1696">spoken</char> <char style="w" strong="H0413">concerning</char> his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>: when I <char style="w" strong="H2490">begin</char>, I will also make an <char style="w" strong="H3615">end</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.12 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">when…: Heb. beginning and ending</char></note> <verse eid="1SA 3:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1SA 3:13" />For I have <char style="w" strong="H5046">told</char> him that I will <char style="w" strong="H8199">judge</char> his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> <char style="w" strong="H5704">for</char> <char style="w" strong="H5769">ever</char> for the <char style="w" strong="H5771">iniquity</char> which he <char style="w" strong="H3045">knoweth</char>; because his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> made themselves <char style="w" strong="H7043">vile</char>, and he <char style="w" strong="H3543">restrained</char> them not.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.13 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">For I…: or, And I will