  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="1SA 6:10" />¶ And the <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> did <char style="w" strong="H6213">so</char>; and <char style="w" strong="H3947">took</char> <char style="w" strong="H8147">two</char> <char style="w" strong="H5763">milch</char> <char style="w" strong="H6510">kine</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0631">tied</char> them to the <char style="w" strong="H5699">cart</char>, and shut <char style="w" strong="H3607">up</char> their <char style="w" strong="H1121">calves</char> at <char style="w" strong="H1004">home</char>: <verse eid="1SA 6:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1SA 6:11" />And they <char style="w" strong="H7760">laid</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0727">ark</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> upon the <char style="w" strong="H5699">cart</char>, and the <char style="w" strong="H0712">coffer</char> with the <char style="w" strong="H5909">mice</char> of <char style="w" strong="H2091">gold</char> and the <char style="w" strong="H6754">images</char> of their <char style="w" strong="H2914">emerods</char>. <verse eid="1SA 6:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1SA 6:12" />And the <char style="w" strong="H6510">kine</char> took the <char style="w" strong="H3474">straight</char> <char style="w" strong="H1870">way</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H1870">way</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1053">Beth-shemesh</char>, <char style="add">and</char> went <char style="w" strong="H1980">along</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4546">highway</char>, <char style="w" strong="H1600">lowing</char> as they <char style="w" strong="H1980">went</char>, and turned not <char style="w" strong="H5493">aside</char> <char style="add">to</char> the right <char style="w" strong="H3225">hand</char> or <char style="add">to</char> the <char style="w" strong="H8040">left</char>; and the <char style="w" strong="H5633">lords</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines