  <para style="p">
    <verse number="24" style="v" sid="1SA 14:24" />¶ And the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> were <char style="w" strong="H5065">distressed</char> that <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>: for <char style="w" strong="H7586">Saul</char> had <char style="w" strong="H0422">adjured</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0779">Cursed</char> <char style="add">be</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> that <char style="w" strong="H0398">eateth</char> <char style="add">any</char> <char style="w" strong="H3899">food</char> until <char style="w" strong="H6153">evening</char>, that I may be <char style="w" strong="H5358">avenged</char> on mine <char style="w" strong="H0341">enemies</char>. So none of the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H2938">tasted</char> <char style="add">any</char> <char style="w" strong="H3899">food</char>. <verse eid="1SA 14:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="1SA 14:25" />And all <char style="add">they of</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> to a <char style="w" strong="H3293">wood</char>; and there was <char style="w" strong="H1706">honey</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">upon</char> the <char style="w" strong="H7704">ground</char>. <verse eid="1SA 14:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="1SA 14:26" />And when the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> were <char style="w" strong="H0935">come</char> into the <char style="w" strong="H3293">wood</char>, behold, the <char style="w" strong="H1706">honey</char> <char style="w" strong="H1982">dropped</char>; but no man <char style="w" strong="H5381">put</char> his <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> to his <char style="w" strong="H6310">mouth</char>: for the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H