    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="1SA 17:4" />¶ And there went <char style="w" strong="H3318">out</char> a <char style="w" strong="H0376">champion</char> out of the <char style="w" strong="H4264">camp</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines</char>, <char style="w" strong="H8034">named</char> <char style="w" strong="H1555">Goliath</char>, of <char style="w" strong="H1661">Gath</char>, whose <char style="w" strong="H1363">height</char> <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H8337">six</char> <char style="w" strong="H0520">cubits</char> and a <char style="w" strong="H2239">span</char>. <verse eid="1SA 17:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1SA 17:5" />And <char style="add">he had</char> an <char style="w" strong="H3553">helmet</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5178">brass</char> upon his <char style="w" strong="H7218">head</char>, and he <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H3847">armed</char> with a <char style="w" strong="H8302">coat</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7193">mail</char>; and the <char style="w" strong="H4948">weight</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H8302">coat</char> <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H2568">five</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H8255">shekels</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5178">brass</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">17.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">armed: Heb. clothed</char></note> <verse eid="1SA 17:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1SA 17:6" />And <char style="add">he had</char> <char style="w" strong="H4697">greaves</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5178">brass</char> upon his <char style="w" strong="H7272">legs</char>, and a <char style="w" strong="H3591">target</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5178">brass</char> between his <char style="w" strong="H3802">shoulders</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">17.6 </char><char style="f