  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1SA 23:1" />Then they <char style="w" strong="H5046">told</char> <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, Behold, the <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines</char> <char style="w" strong="H3898">fight</char> against <char style="w" strong="H7084">Keilah</char>, and they <char style="w" strong="H8154">rob</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1637">threshingfloors</char>. <verse eid="1SA 23:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1SA 23:2" />Therefore <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H7592">enquired</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, Shall I <char style="w" strong="H3212">go</char> and <char style="w" strong="H5221">smite</char> these <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines</char>? And the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3212">Go</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5221">smite</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H3467">save</char> <char style="w" strong="H7084">Keilah</char>. <verse eid="1SA 23:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1SA 23:3" />And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto him, Behold, we be <char style="w" strong="H3373">afraid</char> here in <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char>: how much more then if we <char style="w" strong="H3212">come</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7084">Keilah</char> against the <char style="w" strong="H4634">armies</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H6430">Philistines</char>? <verse eid="1SA 23:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1SA 23:4" />Then <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style