    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="1SA 25:32" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> to <char style="w" strong="H0026">Abigail</char>, <char style="w" strong="H1288">Blessed</char> <char style="add">be</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, which <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> thee this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7125">meet</char> me: <verse eid="1SA 25:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="1SA 25:33" />And <char style="w" strong="H1288">blessed</char> <char style="add">be</char> thy <char style="w" strong="H2940">advice</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H1288">blessed</char> <char style="add">be</char> thou, which hast <char style="w" strong="H3607">kept</char> me this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> from <char style="w" strong="H0935">coming</char> to <char style="add">shed</char> <char style="w" strong="H1818">blood</char>, and from <char style="w" strong="H3467">avenging</char> myself with mine own <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char>. <verse eid="1SA 25:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="1SA 25:34" />For in very <char style="w" strong="H0199">deed</char>, <char style="add">as</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H2416">liveth</char>, which hath kept me <char style="w" strong="H4513">back</char> from <char style="w" strong="H7489">hurting</char> thee, <char style="w" strong="H3884">except</char> thou hadst <char style="w" strong="H4116">hasted</char> and <char style="w" strong="H0935">come</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7125">meet</char> me, surely there had not been <char style="w" strong="H3498">left</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H503