    <verse number="36" style="v" sid="1SA 25:36" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H0026">Abigail</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> to <char style="w" strong="H5037">Nabal</char>; and, behold, he held a <char style="w" strong="H4960">feast</char> in his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, like the <char style="w" strong="H4960">feast</char> of a <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>; and <char style="w" strong="H5037">Nabal’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H3820">heart</char> <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H2896">merry</char> within him, for he <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H3966">very</char> <char style="w" strong="H7910">drunken</char>: wherefore she <char style="w" strong="H5046">told</char> him <char style="w" strong="H1697">nothing</char>, <char style="w" strong="H6996">less</char> or <char style="w" strong="H1419">more</char>, until the <char style="w" strong="H1242">morning</char> <char style="w" strong="H0216">light</char>. <verse eid="1SA 25:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="1SA 25:37" />But it came to pass in the <char style="w" strong="H1242">morning</char>, when the <char style="w" strong="H3196">wine</char> was gone <char style="w" strong="H3318">out</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5037">Nabal</char>, and his <char style="w" strong="H0802">wife</char> had <char style="w" strong="H5046">told</char> him these <char style="w" strong="H1697">things</char>, that his <char style="w" strong="H3820">heart</char> <char style="w" strong="H4191">died</char> <char style="w" strong="H7130">within</char> him, and he became <char style="add">as</char> a <char style="w" strong="H0068">stone</char>. <verse eid="1SA 25:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="1SA 25:38" />And it came to pass about <char style="w" strong="H6235">ten</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">days</char> <char style="add">after</char>, that the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <cha